<p />
<h3><a name="Cost"></a> Cost </h3>
<p />
The workshop will be FREE to all categories of participants.  
<p />
Full-time students and qualified individuals from outside the Chapel Hill area who seek travel and expense support should indicate their need in the application. A limited amount of such support may be available for transportation and lodging. We expect that most non-student participants will be from the neighboring states and/or have other means of support for the duration of the workshop.
<p />
<h3><a name="Location"></a> Location </h3>
<p />
The workshop will be held Wednesday and Thursday, April 22-23 at the Renaissance Computing Institute (<a href="http://www.renci.org/about/locations/renci-anchor-at-europa-center" target="_top">RENCI</a>), 100 Europa Drive, Chapel Hill.  
We will meet in Biltmore room on the 5th floor of the building. There will be signs from the elevators to the room.
<p />
<h3><a name="Transportation_and_Directions"></a> Transportation and Directions </h3>
<p />
The closest airport is <a href="http://www.rdu.com" target="_top">RDU</a> in. Please see the <a href="http://www.renci.org/about/locations/renci-anchor-at-europa-center" target="_top">visitor's information pages</a> for directions and more information. 
<p />
<h4><a name="Parking"></a> Parking </h4>
<p />
Parking is free.
<p />
<p />
<h3><a name="Accommodation"></a> Accommodation </h3>
<p />
If you are coming from outside the triangle area, a good hotel is <a href="http://www.sheratonchapelhill.com/" target="_top">Sheraton Chapel Hill</a>. Mention "RENCI" when booking your room.
<p />
<h3><a name="Sponsors"></a> Sponsors </h3>
The workshop is supported by the <a href="http://opensciencegrid.org" target="_top">Open Science Grid</a>, a national project funded by the <a href="http://www.er.doe.gov/" target="_top">Department of Energy Office of Science</a> and the <a href="http://nsf.gov" target="_top">National Science Foundation</a>.
